    </wadl:resource>
    <wadl:resource path="/rest/api/collections/search">
      <wadl:method name="POST">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[This service allows to search deviceCollections using a manager containing:<br>
<ul>
<li>pagination parameters,</li>
<li>column to use to sort elements,</li>
<li>direction of sorting</li>
<li>and a filter.</li>
</ul>
For admin or user role, only deviceCollections of caller's company are returned.<br>
If the filter is not properly built or if pagination parameters are inconsistent, an exception is thrown.<br>
DeviceCollections returned have their label.<br>
The result has:<br>
<ul>
<li>number of returned elements</li>
<li>and the list of selected elements.</li>
</ul>]]>
        </wadl:doc>
        <wadl:request>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[the manager containing information used to search deviceCollections]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="paginatedmanager"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:request>
        <wadl:response>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[the selected deviceCollections (empty if there is no result)]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="summary"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:response>
      </wadl:method>
    </wadl:resource>
    <wadl:resource path="/rest/api/collections/update">
      <wadl:method name="POST">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[Update a collection using xml/json input structure.<br>
Only admin and user roles can call this service.<br>
Root is considered as an admin of his company.<br>
A collection contains :<br>
<ul>
<li>an id, it is required and an exception is thrown if it is missing</li>
<li>label, required and must be unique in caller's company (if the given label is changed and already used, an
exception is thrown)</li>
<li>a company, if specified it is ignored and automatically set with caller's company</li>
</ul>
The service returns the collection updated, with all previous attributes.]]>
        </wadl:doc>
        <wadl:request>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[collection to update]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="deviceCollection"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:request>
        <wadl:response>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[collection updated]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="deviceCollection"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:response>
      </wadl:method>
    </wadl:resource>
    <wadl:resource path="/rest/api/company/create">
      <wadl:method name="POST">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[This method provides create a company.<br>
Only root of the platform is allowed to use this method.<br>
Except for the id (which will be automatically set with company's name), all attributes of company are required.
Mandatory attributes are:<br>
<ul>
<li>A name (unique),</li>
<li>A postal address,</li>
<li>An email (respecting the format of an email and not already used); the email is automatically converted in
lowercase letters.</li>
<li>And a phone number.</li>
</ul>
Also:<br>
<ul>
<li>Root can register the company's companyProfile, a map of properties,</li>
<li>An applicationProfile is automatically created and attached to current company</li>
</ul>
Concerning the company's companyProfile, following entries can be specified (the default value is used for
missing entries):<br>
<ul>
<li>AUTO_PROVISIONING_ACCEPTED (default value is YES),</li>
<li>DEVICE_DISPLAYED (default value is YES),</li>
<li>SIM_DISPLAYED (default value is NO),</li>
<li>SECURITY_LEVEL (default value is BASIC_AUTHENTICATION),</li>
<li>MAX_STORED_EVENTS (default value is 10000) and</li>
<li>COMPANY_TOPIC</li>
</ul>
The returned company has an id and all previous attributes (except the applicationProfile).<br>]]>
        </wadl:doc>
        <wadl:request>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[The company to create (JSON/XML structure).]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="company"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:request>
        <wadl:response>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[Returns the company created.]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="company"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:response>
      </wadl:method>
    </wadl:resource>
    <wadl:resource path="/rest/api/company/list">
      <wadl:method name="GET">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[This method returns a list of companies order by name:<br>
<ul>
<li>All companies with pagination parameters for root,</li>
<li>The connected user's company for an admin or a user.</li>
</ul>
Each company returned has:<br>
<ul>
<li>An id,</li>
<li>A name,</li>
<li>A postal address,</li>
<li>An email,</li>
<li>A phone number</li>
<li>And a companyProfile (map of properties).</li>
</ul>
If the result is paginated but pagination parameters are inconsistent, an exception is thrown.
Paginate parameters are not mandatory. Default values are use (see below).]]>
        </wadl:doc>
        <wadl:request>
          <wadl:param name="paginate" style="query">
            <wadl:doc>
              <![CDATA[Boolean which indicates if result is paginated (only for root)]]>
            </wadl:doc>
          </wadl:param>
          <wadl:param name="startIndex" style="query">
            <wadl:doc>
              <![CDATA[The start index in the collection to get]]>
            </wadl:doc>
          </wadl:param>
          <wadl:param name="nbElts" style="query">
            <wadl:doc>
              <![CDATA[Number of elements to return from the start index]]>
            </wadl:doc>
          </wadl:param>
        </wadl:request>
        <wadl:response>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[Returns a collection of companies.]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:response>
      </wadl:method>
    </wadl:resource>
    <wadl:resource path="/rest/api/company/search">
      <wadl:method name="POST">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[This method provides search companies using a paginatedmanager. Paginatedmanager contains:<br>
<ul>
<li>Pagination parameters,</li>
<li>Column to use to sort elements,</li>
<li>Direction of sort</li>
<li>And a filter.</li>
</ul>
This is usable only for root because for admin or user only connected user's company is returned.<br>
If the filter is not properly built or if pagination parameters are inconsistent, an exception is thrown.<br>
Returned companies have:<br>
<ul>
<li>An id,</li>
<li>A name,</li>
<li>A postal address,</li>
<li>An email,</li>
<li>A phone number</li>
<li>And companyProfile (map of properties).</li>
</ul>
The result has:<br>
<ul>
<li>Number of selected elements ignoring pagination</li>
<li>And the list of selected elements.</li>
</ul>]]>
        </wadl:doc>
        <wadl:request>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[PaginatedManager contains information used to search companies]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="paginatedmanager"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:request>
        <wadl:response>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[Returns the selected companies (empty if there is no result).]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="summary"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:response>
      </wadl:method>
    </wadl:resource>
    <wadl:resource path="/rest/api/company/update">
      <wadl:method name="POST">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[This method provides update an existing company.<br>
Root of the platform can update any company.<br>
An admin role can ONLY update attributes of his company, except for values of companyProfile which are read-only.<br>
A user role is NOT allowed to call this method.<br>
All attributes of the company must be specified even if they are
unchanged.<br>
Attributes expected are:<br>
<ul>
<li>An id (which MUST be available),</li>
<li>A name (which can NOT be changed),</li>
<li>A postal address,</li>
<li>An email (it must respect the format of an email and be unique if it is changed); it is automatically
converted in lowercase letters.</li>
<li>And a phone number.</li>
</ul>
If the company's companyProfile (map of properties) is modified, previous values are replaced (ONLY for root).<br>
The returned company has all previous attributes.<br>]]>
        </wadl:doc>
        <wadl:request>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[The company to update (JSON/XML structure).]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="company"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:request>
        <wadl:response>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[Returns the updated company.]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="company"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:response>
      </wadl:method>
    </wadl:resource>
