An admin role can ONLY create other admin roles or user roles, attached to his company.<br>
A user role is NOT allowed to request this method.<br>
All following attributes (except preferences) are required:<br>
<ul>
<li>The id of the user's company,</li>
<li>A login (respecting the format of an email and not already used); the login is automatically converted to
lowercase letters,</li>
<li>A first name,</li>
<li>A last name,</li>
<li>And an available role ("admin" or "user").</li>
</ul>
The creation of the user is also propagated to LDAP.]]>
        </wadl:doc>
        <wadl:request>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[The user to create (JSON/XML structure).]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="user"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:request>
        <wadl:response>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[Returns the created user.]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="user"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:response>
      </wadl:method>
    </wadl:resource>
    <wadl:resource path="/rest/api/user/list">
      <wadl:method name="GET">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[This method returns:<br>
<ul>
<li>All users using the pagination parameters for root,</li>
<li>All users of admin's company for an admin role</li>
<li>And himself for a user role.</li>
</ul>
Each returned user has:<br>
<ul>
<li>A login,</li>
<li>A first name,</li>
<li>A last name,</li>
<li>A role,</li>
<li>His preferences,</li>
<li>And his company (with an id, a name, a postal address, an email, a phone number and a companyProfile)</li>
</ul>
If necessary, a synchronization is operated between platform database and LDAP.<br>
If the result is paginated but pagination parameters are inconsistent, an exception is thrown.
Paginate parameters are not mandatory. Default values are use (see below).]]>
        </wadl:doc>
        <wadl:request>
          <wadl:param name="paginate" style="query">
            <wadl:doc>
              <![CDATA[Boolean which indicates if result is paginated (only for root or admin)]]>
            </wadl:doc>
          </wadl:param>
          <wadl:param name="startIndex" style="query">
            <wadl:doc>
              <![CDATA[The start index in the collection to get]]>
            </wadl:doc>
          </wadl:param>
          <wadl:param name="nbElts" style="query">
            <wadl:doc>
              <![CDATA[Number of elements to get from the start index]]>
            </wadl:doc>
          </wadl:param>
        </wadl:request>
        <wadl:response>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[Returns a collection of users.]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:response>
      </wadl:method>
    </wadl:resource>
    <wadl:resource path="/rest/api/user/search">
      <wadl:method name="POST">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[This method provides search users using a manager containing:<br>
<ul>
<li>Pagination parameters,</li>
<li>Column to use to sort elements,</li>
<li>Direction of sorting</li>
<li>And a filter.</li>
</ul>
This is usable only for root and admin because for user only himself is returned.<br>
If the filter is not properly built or if pagination parameters are inconsistent, an exception is thrown.<br>
Returned users have:<br>
<ul>
<li>A login,</li>
<li>A first name,</li>
<li>A last name,</li>
<li>A role,</li>
<li>His preferences</li>
<li>And his company (with an id, a name, a postal address, an email, a phone number and a companyProfile)</li>
</ul>
The result has:<br>
<ul>
<li>Number of selected elements ignoring pagination</li>
<li>And the list of selected elements.</li>
</ul>
If necessary, a synchronization is operated between platform database and LDAP.]]>
        </wadl:doc>
        <wadl:request>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[The manager containing information used to search users]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="paginatedmanager"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:request>
        <wadl:response>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[Returns the selected users (empty if there is no result).]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="summary"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:response>
      </wadl:method>
    </wadl:resource>
    <wadl:resource path="/rest/api/user/update">
      <wadl:method name="POST">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[WARNING: This method can be requested ONLY if the platform is configured with EOBJECT_DRIVEN ldap mode.<br>
This method provides update an existing user.<br>
Root of the platform is allowed to:<br>
<ul>
<li>Update himself except his login and his role,</li>
<li>Update any admin role or user role attributes except their login (update a role to "root" is forbidden)</li>
</ul>
An admin role can update any user of his company.<br>
A user role can ONLY update himself except his login and his role.<br>
All attributes of the user (except his preferences) must be specified, even if they are unchanged:<br>
<ul>
<li>The id of the user's company,</li>
<li>The login of the user,</li>
<li>A first name,</li>
<li>A last name,</li>
<li>And a role (which must be "admin" or "user", except for root),</li>
</ul>
If the user's preferences are updated, they will be persisted.<br>
Except for preferences, user's attributes are updated on LDAP.<br>
The returned user has all previous attributes and his preferences.<br>]]>
        </wadl:doc>
        <wadl:request>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[The user to update (JSON/XML structure).]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="user"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:request>
        <wadl:response>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[Returns the updated user.]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="user"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:response>
      </wadl:method>
    </wadl:resource>
