    <wadl:resource path="/rest/api/gateways/{deviceId}/{serviceName}/{actionName}/subscribe">
      <wadl:param name="deviceId" style="template">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[id of the device concerned by the subscription]]>
        </wadl:doc>
      </wadl:param>
      <wadl:param name="serviceName" style="template">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[name of service containing the action]]>
        </wadl:doc>
      </wadl:param>
      <wadl:param name="actionName" style="template">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[name of the action to subscribe]]>
        </wadl:doc>
      </wadl:param>
      <wadl:method name="POST">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[This method provides subscribe to a service/action of a gateway.<br>
Root of the platform can subscribe to any service/action of any gateway.<br>
An admin/a user role can ONLY subscribe to a service/action of his company's gateway.<br>
The input subscription structure (XML/JSON) is used:<br>
<ul>
<li>id, it is ignored and automatically generated</li>
<li>date, it is ignored and automaticcally set to time of subscription creation</li>
<li>duration (in hour), if not specified (or if the given value is less than 1), it is set to -1 which means that
the subscription has an infinite duration</li>
<li>status, it is ignored and set to PENDING by default</li>
<li>application-profile id, it is required and if it is unavailable, a WEBApplicationException is thrown</li>
<li>action, it is ignored and determined with path parameters (gatewayId, serviceName and actionName)</li>
<li>actionValues, represents the arguments to give to the target action</li>
</ul>
The status of the subscription is PENDING by default. Then, a SUBSCRIPTION message is sent to the gateway with
the same duration as subscription and with actionValues given. When the RESPONSE of subscription from the gateway
is received, the status became ACTIVATED and EVENT message from the gateway are sent to COMPANY_TOPIC defined in
companyProfile. When currentDate is greater than subscriptionCreationDate + duration, the
subscription status became DEACTIVATED (stopped).]]>
        </wadl:doc>
        <wadl:request>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[information relative to the subscription]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="subscription"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:request>
        <wadl:response>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[the subscription stored]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="subscription"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:response>
      </wadl:method>
    </wadl:resource>
