    <wadl:resource path="/rest/api/gateways/{deviceId}/{serviceName}/{actionName}/renewal/{subscriptionId}">
      <wadl:param name="deviceId" style="template">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[id of the device concerned by the renewal]]>
        </wadl:doc>
      </wadl:param>
      <wadl:param name="serviceName" style="template">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[name of service of the target gateway]]>
        </wadl:doc>
      </wadl:param>
      <wadl:param name="actionName" style="template">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[name of target action]]>
        </wadl:doc>
      </wadl:param>
      <wadl:param name="subscriptionId" style="template">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[id of the subscription to renewal]]>
        </wadl:doc>
      </wadl:param>
      <wadl:method name="POST">
        <wadl:doc>
          <![CDATA[Renewal to an action of a service of a gateway.<br>
Admin/user role of a company can renewal to an action of his company's gateway.<br>
For a renewal, there are 2 cases depending on subscription's status:<br>
<ul>
<li>ACTIVATED : in this case, the given duration is added to current duration (if current duration is -1, the
given duration is ignored)</li>
<li>DEACTIVATED : in this case, date of subscription is set to date of renewal and status became PENDING until
the RESPONSE of renewalled subscription from the gateway is received</li>
</ul>
In both cases, you can set duration to -1 to have an infinite subscription.<br>
A RENEWAL message is sent to the gateway with updated information.<br>]]>
        </wadl:doc>
        <wadl:request>
          <wadl:param name="duration" style="query">
            <wadl:doc>
              <![CDATA[duration in hour of renewal]]>
            </wadl:doc>
          </wadl:param>
        </wadl:request>
        <wadl:response>
          <wadl:doc>
            <![CDATA[the subscription renewalled]]>
          </wadl:doc>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="text/xml" element="subscription"/>
          <wadl:representation mediaType="application/json"/>
        </wadl:response>
      </wadl:method>
    </wadl:resource>
